verses.roman:
saubhary-ādi-prāya sei kāya-vyūha naya
kāya-vyūha haile nāradera vismaya nā haya

synonyms: saubhari-ādi—beginning with the sage named Saubhari; prāya—like; sei—that; kāya-vyūha—the expansion of one's body; naya—is not; kāya-vyūha—expansions of the body; haile—if there are; nāradera—of Nārada Muni; vismaya—the astonishment; nā haya—there cannot be.
translation: "The prābhava-prakāśa expansions of Lord Kṛṣṇa are not like the expansions of the sage Saubhari. Had they been so, Nārada would not have been astonished to see them.
